### Service Learning and Youth Civic Engagement (continued)

- **"Service learning"** refers to community service coupled to classwork, believed more effective at inculcating civic habits than standalone service
- **1999 youth service statistics**: ~57% of U.S. students in grades 6-12 participated in community service (up from 49% in 1996)
  - However, slightly more than half of them (30% of all students) engaged in **service learning** specifically
- Source: "Youth Service-Learning and Community Service among 6th- through 12th-Grade Students in the United States, 1996 and 1999" (National Center for Education Statistics, 1999)

