- **Rafe Sagalyn** (literary agent): "sturdy thick-and-thin friend and guide," channeling enthusiasms toward publishable manuscript
- **Nick Mitropoulos**: embodied "classic Hellenic virtues of good friendship and good citizenship along with the classic Beantown virtues of loyalty and connections"—provided encouragement and problem-solving throughout the decade
- **Angela Glover Blackwell** (vice president of Rockefeller Foundation): skeptical about aspects of argument but provided crucial support, helping author understand her insights
- **Michael Bruno** (vice president): [entry continues on next page]

